This package draws inspiration from `pi-agent` (https://github.com/earendil-works/pi)
by Mario Zechner, also MIT-licensed. The Go-native API (iterator-based events,
buffered steering channel, minimal three-hook surface) is an independent
re-design for Go; the high-level loop shape (input -> tool calls -> response,
hook ordering, steering at iteration boundary) follows the upstream's lead.
